    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix VNF Process Startup Error Handling in Integration Tests\n\n### Summary\nThe `start_vnf_proc()` function in the open-nFAPI integration tests was not properly handling process creation failures, leading to test hangs and unclear error reporting. When the VNF simulator executable was missing or failed to start, the function would return an invalid PID without any error indication, causing subsequent test operations to fail silently or hang indefinitely.\n\nThe issue was particularly evident when running integration tests in environments where the VNF simulator had not been built, or when incorrect paths were specified. The function also lacked proper error propagation for fork() and execv() failures, making debugging difficult.\n\nThis fix improves error handling throughout the process management functions and ensures tests gracefully handle startup failures.\n\n### Changes\n- `nfapi/open-nFAPI/integration_tests/main.cpp`: \n  - Added proper error handling for fork() failure in `start_vnf_proc()` and `start_pnf_proc()`\n  - Added exit code propagation for execv() failures\n  - Added validation checks in test functions to handle process startup failures\n  - Enhanced `kill_proc()` with input validation and error reporting\n  - Added missing includes for errno.h and signal.h\n"
}